sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2142005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Composite part containing inducible mazF toxin and dam metylase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part was the attacking part of our fighting system. It allowed to induce the fighting system simple by adding IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lukas Rieder
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part had to be inducible. Later we figured out that it was not that smart to use the same RBS because E.coli did recombination.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K731500
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: [LacI + LacIq promoter] reverse + [tac promoter + lac operator] forward
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is E.coli lactose-inducibile promoter.
lac repressor (encoded from lacI gene) is the regulator protein: in absence of lactose the protein binds to lac operator, preventing RNA-polymerase binding and transcription. Low, constitutive levels of transcription can be seen anyhow.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Francesco Guzzonato

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2142003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part forms in combination with the part BBa_K2142001 toxin/antitoxin system for selection. This toxin digest mRNA so that E.coli can nor grow anymore. We used it in combination with the antitoxin to let bacteria fight against each other.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lukas Rieder
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The problem with this part is that e.coli does not like to produce toxic stuff so we combined it with a strong promoter which can be induced.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2142004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This coding sequence was used to generate a higher mutation rate. Norma this protein is used as repairing system. With overexpression its possible to reach a mutation rate which is 50x more than normal. Mutation will occur on plasmid and genom.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lukas Rieder
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Is on the genom of bacteria to methylate new synthesized DNA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The achieve a over expression we used a strong constitutive promoter.
